@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> May 17, 2025
    </div>

    <p class="lead">
        At RepTrack, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information.
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our workout tracking application.
    </p>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Information We Collect</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h6">Personal Information</h3>
            <p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your name and email address</li>
                <li>Authentication information (password, securely stored using industry-standard hashing)</li>
                <li>Optional profile information if provided</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h6">Workout Data</h3>
            <p>As you use RepTrack, we collect:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Workout details (date, type, exercises)</li>
                <li>Exercise performance data (sets, reps, weight, RPE)</li>
                <li>Goals and progress metrics</li>
                <li>Personal notes related to workouts</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h6">Usage Information</h3>
            <p>We automatically collect certain information about how you use our application:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Log data (such as IP address, browser type, and pages visited)</li>
                <li>Device information (operating system, hardware model, and unique device identifiers)</li>
                <li>Usage patterns and feature interaction</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="h5 mb-0">How We Use Your Information</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the RepTrack application</li>
                <li>Create and manage your account</li>
                <li>Process and complete your requested actions</li>
                <li>Generate analytics and insights about your workout performance</li>
                <li>Communicate with you about your account, updates, and new features</li>
                <li>Ensure the security and integrity of our application</li>
                <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve user experience</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>RepTrack does not sell your personal information. We may share your information in the following situations:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> When you explicitly choose to share workout data with other users or coaches through our platform.</li>
                <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share data with trusted third-party service providers who help us operate, maintain, and improve our application.</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose information if required by law, legal process, or governmental request.</li>
                <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as a business asset.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Data Security</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Encryption of sensitive data both in transit and at rest</li>
                <li>Regular security assessments and updates</li>
                <li>Access controls and authentication procedures</li>
                <li>Secure data storage practices</li>
            </ul>
            <p>However, please note that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>You have several rights regarding your personal information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access and Update:</strong> You can access and update your account information through your profile settings.</li>
                <li><strong>Data Export:</strong> You can request a copy of your workout data in a structured, commonly used format.</li>
                <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can request deletion of your account and associated data.</li>
                <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> You can opt out of promotional communications by adjusting your notification settings.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise these rights, please contact us at reptrack@example.com.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.</p>
            <p>We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Contact Us</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:</p>
            <p>
                RepTrack<br>
                reptrack@example.com
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>